\cf2 \cb4 1. Small is beautiful.\cb1 \
\cb4 2. Make each program do one thing well.\cb1 \
\cb4 3. Build a prototype as soon as possible.\cb1 \
\cb4 4. Choose portability over efficiency.\cb1 \
\cb4 5. Store data in flat text files.\cb1 \
\cb4 6. Use software leverage to your advantage.\cb1 \
\cb4 7. Use shell scripts to increase leverage and portability.\cb1 \
\cb4 8. Avoid captive user interfaces.\cb1 \
\cb4 9. Make every program a filter.\cb1 \
