{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://dhdebates.gc.cuny.edu/#en0912r"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 \cb4 12.}}\cb4 \'a0To be fair, Newfield also explores a more radical impulse in literary study in the period, evident in the likes of (surprisingly) both Harold Bloom and Raymond Williams. This impulse valued literature precisely in its ability to offer an \'93unmanaged exploration of experience\'94 (152).\cb1 \
